    {
      "id": "p008",
      "index": 8,
      "source": "Microsoft reported two power consumption figures, one with both analog and digital system power, and one with only analog power. The latter is what most die-to-die interconnects report. At 24 Gb/s, the system power is 0.33 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.226 pJ/b, while at 20 Gb/s, the system power is 0.25 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.17 pJ/b. The power at idle state is 0.05 pJ/b.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0296",
      "parent_block_index": 296,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "Microsoft reported two power consumption figures, one with both analog and digital system power, and one with only analog power. The latter is what most die-to-die interconnects report. At 24 Gb/s, the system power is 0.33 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.226 pJ/b, while at 20 Gb/s, the system power is 0.25 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.17 pJ/b. The power at idle state is 0.05 pJ/b.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "Microsoft reported two power consumption figures, one with both analog and digital system power, and one with only analog power. The latter is what most die-to-die interconnects report. At 24 Gb/s, the system power is 0.33 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.226 pJ/b, while at 20 Gb/s, the system power is 0.25 pJ/b and the analog power is 0.17 pJ/b. The power at idle state is 0.05 pJ/b.",
